&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/science/domains/biology/domains/physiology/terms/homeostasis/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/science/domains/biology/domains/physiology/terms/homeostasis/> ;
  schema:name "Homeostasis" ;
  schema:description "Homeostasis is the maintenance of relatively stable internal conditions in a living system despite changes in the external environment. The term was coined by Walter Cannon in 1926, drawing on Claude Bernard's earlier concept of the *milieu intérieur* — the idea that the internal environment of an organism must remain constant for life to continue." ;
